          <mods:abstract xml:lang="en">
            The model depicts the Volpa Synagogue, a wooden baroque synagogue formerly located in present-day Belarus,
            in its interwar phase shortly before destruction by the German occupiers. The reconstruction is based on
            archival inventory drawings, historic photographs and the monograph by Maria and Kazimierz Piechotka on
            wooden synagogues of the former Polish–Lithuanian Commonwealth. It was created as a student project at the
            Warsaw University of Technology within the PL 3DREKO-22 seminar coordinated by the Institute of
            Architecture of Mainz University of Applied Sciences.
          </mods:abstract>
          <mods:note type="description" xml:lang="en">
            3D reconstruction of the wooden Volpa Synagogue as it stood between 1929 and 1941, based mainly on archival
            drawings and photographs and created within the PL 3DREKO-22 teaching project.
          </mods:note>

          <mods:note type="representationStatus">
            Interpretative historical reconstruction of a destroyed object (past phase, 1929–1941).
          </mods:note>
          <mods:note type="phaseName">
            Interwar phase before destruction (1929–1941).
          </mods:note>
          <mods:note type="representationalMode">
            Hybrid: evidence-based geometry with hypothetical or symbolic materials.
          </mods:note>
          <mods:note type="creationMethod">
            Manual polygonal modelling of architecture and interior from historic drawings and photographs.
          </mods:note>
          <mods:note type="methodology">
            Manual modelling of architecture and decorative elements from inventory drawings and historic photographs;
            UV unwrapping and texturing; export to GLB for web visualisation.
          </mods:note>
          <mods:note type="aiInvolvement">
            No AI or machine learning methods were used in the modelling process.
          </mods:note>
          <mods:note type="interventionType">
            Virtual reconstruction (restitution of lost architecture) in the sense of the Seville Principles.
          </mods:note>

